  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "It's clear once you run `next` against a test suite of any size that tripling the call overhead for `truffle-contract` is not that great. Two fixes seem necessary:\r\n\r\n+ The check for network specified gas values / `auto-gas: off` [here](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/next/packages/truffle-contract/lib/execute.js#L39-L40) needs to be moved back before the gas estimate call. This was accidentally put inside the promise callback during the reason string work. \r\n+ The reason strings could be post-fetched on error so that successful txs don't incur any overhead. There are potential issues with this (both account and block number state can be materially changed after a tx failure). It's not great. On the other hand post-fetch maps more closely to the strategy Geth / Parity are proposing for making this data available - namely that return data is kept in a client cache which is indexed by txHash and a special RPC call exists to fetch it.\r\n",
